meowtrics (0.2.2-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Plasmoid widget renders Oneko sprites
    - Replaced the static emoji Text element in CompactRepresentation.qml
      with an Image driven by a frame timer, mirroring the SNI tray's
      sprite engine. Six animations (sleep / sit_calm / sit_alert /
      wash_face / run_panic / scratch), per-frame durations exactly
      matching src/sprites.rs.
    - Sprites are tinted to Kirigami.Theme.textColor via ColorOverlay
      so they read on both Breeze Light and Breeze Dark panels.
    - The popup (FullRepresentation) shows a 96x96 version of the same
      animation, the catchy headline, and the per-sensor table.
  * New CLI: `meowtrics tray-state`
    - Emits pre-classified JSON: { animation, headline, sensors[] }.
      The plasmoid is now a dumb renderer; sensor priority and animation
      mapping live in the daemon (single source of truth, mirrors the
      logic the SNI tray uses).

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Wed, 06 May 2026 00:30:00 +0000

meowtrics (0.2.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Sprite alpha was wrong
    - The XBM-to-PNG conversion in v0.2.0 produced 1-bit grayscale PNGs
      with no alpha, which rendered as solid black-square backgrounds.
      Reconverted to true RGBA with the cat opaque and the rest fully
      transparent.
  * Tray ink colour
    - Switched the tray's runtime recolor from white to mid-gray (#808080).
      White was invisible on light panels; mid-gray reads on both light
      and dark themes. v0.3 may add a config option for custom ink.
  * Pages preview
    - Removed the debug "sit_alert" / "sleep" labels that snuck through.
      The hero now shows just the animated cat, no text.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Wed, 06 May 2026 00:10:00 +0000

meowtrics (0.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Animated Oneko cat in the tray
    - Bundled the public-domain Oneko sprite set (32 frames, 32x32 each,
      ~130 KB) under /usr/share/meowtrics/icons/neko/.
    - New SpriteLibrary loads PNG frames at startup and exposes named
      animations: sleep, sit_calm, sit_alert, wash_face, run_panic,
      scratch.
    - SNI tray now ships ARGB pixmaps instead of freedesktop icon names.
      The daemon advances the current animation's frame every 250 ms;
      the cat is actually moving in your tray now.
    - Sensor states map to animations: idle/fresh/long/ancient -> sleep;
      normal/charging/full -> sit_calm; busy/warm/filling -> sit_alert;
      high/hot/low -> wash_face (the cat sweats); critical -> run_panic.
    - If the sprite directory is missing (e.g. stripped install), the
      daemon transparently falls back to the v0.1 themed-icon path.
  * Licensing
    - LICENSING.md documents the Oneko sprite provenance and public-domain
      status (Tatsuya Kato, 1990; verified via Debian's authoritative
      copyright file).

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Tue, 05 May 2026 23:55:00 +0000

meowtrics (0.1.4-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Tray priority: never let "boring forever" sensors win the icon
    - uptime locked to "ancient" after a week and the tray was stuck on the
      uptime icon forever. Boring states (idle, fresh, full, long, ancient,
      off, cool) are now excluded from the icon-priority race; they only win
      if literally nothing else is reporting.
  * Tray tooltip shows every sensor
    - The hover tooltip now lists all sensors with their emoji, state, and
      value, not just the headline message. The active sensor's prose
      message stays as the first line.
  * postinst: refresh plasmashell on upgrade
    - On `apt install --reinstall` or version upgrade, the postinst now
      runs `kquitapp6 plasmashell && kstart plasmashell` for any user with
      an active session, so the new plasmoid QML is picked up without
      manual intervention. Fresh installs skip this since there's no cached
      copy to invalidate.
  * postinst: restart the daemon on upgrade
    - The user-service start-on-install now uses `restart` instead of
      `start`, so an upgrade picks up the new binary even when the unit is
      already active.
  * messages.json: cat narrator, more variety
    - Trimmed sensor list to the 8 actually implemented (cpu, ram, swap,
      thermal, battery, disk, load, uptime). Other sensors will reappear
      when their reader code lands.
    - Rewrote message templates from the cat's POV. 4-7 weighted lines per
      state, ~180 total templates. Tooltip will pick a random one each
      tick and the user actually sees variety now.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Tue, 05 May 2026 23:20:00 +0000

meowtrics (0.1.3-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fatal panic on startup
    - The ksni Tray trait methods are sync, called from inside ksni's tokio
      runtime. v0.1.2 used tokio::sync::RwLock and called blocking_read()
      from those methods, which tokio refuses with "Cannot block the current
      thread from within a runtime". The daemon SIGABRT'd on every startup,
      crash-looping forever and breaking the SNI tray icon.
    - Switched the tray-state lock to std::sync::RwLock. The state is one
      small struct updated once per tick, no real contention.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Tue, 05 May 2026 22:45:00 +0000

meowtrics (0.1.2-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Daemon never started after install
    - The systemd user unit had hardening directives (ProtectSystem,
      ProtectHome, PrivateTmp, MemoryDenyWriteExecute, SystemCallFilter)
      that require CAP_SYS_ADMIN and fail with status=218/CAPABILITIES
      under the user manager. Stripped to NoNewPrivileges, RestrictRealtime,
      LockPersonality only.
    - Result: SNI tray icon now actually appears (the daemon needs to run
      to register the StatusNotifierItem; previously it was crash-looping).
  * Plasmoid imports updated to Plasma 6 conventions
    - Replaced versioned imports ("org.kde.plasma.plasmoid 2.0",
      "QtQuick 2.15") with the Plasma 6 form (no version, "QtQuick").
    - With the old versioned import the loaded module silently downgraded
      to a Plasma 5 PlasmoidItem that has no toolTipMainText/toolTipSubText
      properties, hence the load error "Cannot assign to non-existent
      property toolTipSubText".
  * Plasmoid icon
    - Use the icon-theme name "meowtrics" instead of a Qt.resolvedUrl
      file:// path. The PNG is shipped to /usr/share/icons/hicolor.
  * Auto-enable the user service on install
    - postinst now creates ~/.config/systemd/user/graphical-session.target.wants/
      meowtrics.service for every real user (UID >= 1000) and starts the unit
      immediately for any user with an active session, so `apt install meowtrics`
      is enough; no manual `systemctl --user enable --now meowtrics` step.
    - postrm tears the symlinks back down on remove and stops the unit; purge
      additionally clears per-user config and cache.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Tue, 05 May 2026 22:30:00 +0000

meowtrics (0.1.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Plasma 6 plasmoid fixes
    - Replace Plasma 5 toolTipMainText/SubText with Plasma 6 toolTipMainText
      properties at PlasmoidItem level (the old form errored at load).
    - Plasmoid icon: use the meowtrics logo (shipped at
      /usr/share/icons/hicolor/512x512/apps/meowtrics.png) instead of the
      generic face-smile system icon.
    - Wire Plasma5Support DataSource to actually call `meowtrics json`
      and update the popup sensor list every 5s.
  * Tray icon variation
    - Map (sensor, state) to a wider set of distinct freedesktop icon names
      so the tray icon visibly changes between sensor states.
  * Packaging
    - Build .deb installs the logo to hicolor at 512x512.
    - postinst refreshes the icon cache and runs kbuildsycoca6 so the widget
      shows up in the chooser without re-login.
    - postrm purge clears per-user state in ~/.config/meowtrics and
      ~/.cache/meowtrics for every real user on the system.

